overview: 'The user initiated an urgent request to fix a pull request with
  multiple issues, including critical security flaws and breaking Vercel
  deploys. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the PR comments and CI logs,
  identifying a range of problems from forgeable authentication cookies and
  insecure API pagination to PDF calculation errors and UI bugs. The approach
  involved systematically addressing each issue: first, confirming and resolving
  lint errors that were causing build failures, then implementing a robust
  HMAC-based session management system to fix the authentication vulnerability.
  The agent also added input validation and pagination to API routes to prevent
  memory exhaustion, corrected PDF generation logic for accurate sleep metrics
  and dynamic user names, enhanced number input fields to handle nulls, and
  integrated a "Download PDF" button. Finally, time field validation was added
  to the Zod schema. After verifying all fixes with local lint and TypeScript
  checks, the agent selectively committed the relevant code changes, ensuring a
  secure and functional application.'
